{
  "doc_id": "45855",
  "text": "The stiffness of the large elastic arteries in cardiothoracic (central) circulation increases with age in adult humans, although the muscular peripheral arteries are not obviously affected [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The increase in central arterial stiffness results in progressive age-associated elevations in systolic blood pressure (SBP) and pulse pressure (PP) (5-7). Importantly, the increases in SBP and PP after age 50 are much greater in women than in men [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
